Thabang Moroe will take office with immediate effect and will serve a three year contract as CEO. JOHANNESBURG - Thabang Moroe will officially be the chief executive officer of Cricket South Africa on a permanent basis after he had been acting in the role in the past year following the departure of Haroon Lorgat last year. Lorgat had stepped down as the CEO of South African cricket's governing body following the failed attempt at launching the Global League T20 last year. The tournament has now been revamped and is expected to take off in November this year. Moroe will take office with immediate effect and will serve a three year contract as CEO.